column2: Jack in the Box, Inc. engages in operating and franchising a chain of quick-service and fast-casual restaurants. The company is headquartered in San Diego, California and currently employs 5,200 full-time employees. The firm segment is Jack in the Box. The company has more then 2,200 restaurants in 21 states and Guam. Jack in the Box is a hamburger chain, which offers a selection of products, including classic burgers such as, Jumbo Jack burgers, and new product lines, such as Buttery Jack burgers, and its Brunchfast menu. The company also offers tacos, regular and curly fries, specialty sandwiches, salads and real ice cream shakes, among others. The company also allows its guests to customize meals, as well as order any product at any time of the day or night, including breakfast items. The firm's Jack in the Box QSRs also has the concept of drive-in restaurants. Its Jack in the Box restaurants have seating capacities, ranging from 20 to 100 people.
